entities.name: Rivendell
entities.summary: The Last Homely House East of the Sea, an elven refuge founded by Elrond
entities.description: Hidden valley in the foothills of the Misty Mountains, home to Elrond and a sanctuary for travelers. Known for its architecture, healing houses, and role in major events.

entities.name: The One Ring
entities.summary: The master ring forged by Sauron to control all other rings of power
entities.description: A golden ring that grants invisibility to its bearer but corrupts them over time
entities.history: Forged by Sauron in Mount Doom during the Second Age to control all other Rings of Power

entities.name: The Shire
entities.summary: Homeland of the Hobbits in northwestern Middle-earth
entities.description: A peaceful, fertile region inhabited by Hobbits, known for its rolling hills and pastoral farms
entities.culture: Hobbit society focused on comfort, food, and simple living

entities.name: The Fellowship of the Ring
entities.summary: A group of nine companions chosen to help destroy the One Ring
entities.description: A company of nine members representing the Free Peoples of Middle-earth
beliefs: The One Ring must be destroyed

entities.name: War of the Ring
entities.summary: The great conflict at the end of the Third Age
entities.description: The final war against Sauron that determined the fate of Middle-earth
consequences: Beginning of the Age of Men

entities.name: Third Age
entities.summary: The Third Age of Middle-earth, ending with the War of the Ring
entities.description: The age marked by the rise and fall of Sauron and the end of the dominion of the Elves
majorChanges: Rise and fall of Arnor and Gondor

entities.name: Aragorn
entities.summary: The heir of Isildur who became King of the Reunited Kingdom
entities.biography: Born as Aragorn II, he was raised in Rivendell as Estel. He became chieftain of the Dúnedain and later crowned as King Elessar of the Reunited Kingdom.

entities.name: Gondor
entities.summary: The great kingdom of Men in the South of Middle-earth
entities.description: The greatest realm of Men in the Third Age, founded by Elendil and his sons
beliefs: Defense against the forces of Mordor
Loyalty to the line of kings
traditions: Stewardship in absence of the king

entities.name: Minas Tirith
entities.summary: The great citadel and capital city of Gondor
entities.description: A seven-tiered fortress-city built into Mount Mindolluin, serving as the capital of Gondor
entities.culture: Gondorian society focused on military tradition and preservation of ancient knowledge

entities.name: Siege of Minas Tirith
entities.summary: The great battle for the capital of Gondor during the War of the Ring
entities.description: A major battle where the forces of Mordor besieged Minas Tirith, culminating in the arrival of the Rohirrim and Aragorn's forces

entities.name: Andúril
entities.summary: The reforged sword of Elendil, wielded by Aragorn
entities.description: The reforged shards of Narsil, the sword that cut the One Ring from Sauron's hand
entities.history: Originally known as Narsil, broken in the battle against Sauron, reforged by the elves of Rivendell for Aragorn

entities.name: Samwise Gamgee
entities.summary: Frodo's loyal friend and companion throughout the quest to destroy the One Ring
entities.biography: A hobbit from the Shire who served as Frodo's gardener and became his most trusted companion. Known for his unwavering loyalty and bravery.

entities.name: Mordor
entities.summary: The dark realm of Sauron in the southeast of Middle-earth
entities.description: A barren, volcanic realm surrounded by mountain ranges, home to Sauron's fortress of Barad-dûr and Mount Doom
entities.culture: Dominated by evil forces and organized around military might

entities.name: Mount Doom
entities.summary: The volcano where the One Ring was forged and ultimately destroyed
entities.description: An active volcano in Mordor where Sauron forged the One Ring and the only place where it could be destroyed

entities.name: Second Age
entities.summary: The age of Númenor's glory and the forging of the Rings of Power
entities.description: The age marked by the rise and fall of Númenor and the forging of the Rings of Power
majorChanges: Forging of the Rings of Power
Last Alliance of Elves and Men

entities.name: Sauron
entities.summary: The Dark Lord who created the One Ring
entities.biography: Originally a Maia of Aulë, corrupted by Melkor, became the second Dark Lord of Middle-earth

entities.name: First Age
entities.summary: The First Age of the Sun, marked by the wars against Morgoth
entities.description: The age of the first rising of the Sun and Moon, the awakening of Men, and the great wars against Morgoth in Beleriand
majorChanges: First rising of the Sun and Moon
culturalCharacteristics: Height of Elven kingdoms in Middle-earth
First contact between Elves and Men

entities.name: Fourth Age
entities.summary: The Age of Men, beginning after the destruction of the One Ring
entities.description: The age marked by the dominion of Men and the fading of the Elves from Middle-earth
majorChanges: Rise of the Dominion of Men

entities.name: Galadriel
entities.summary: The Lady of Lothlórien, bearer of Nenya
entities.biography: One of the greatest of the Eldar in Middle-earth, ruler of Lothlórien alongside Celeborn

entities.name: Lothlórien
entities.summary: The golden forest realm of Galadriel and Celeborn
entities.description: An enchanted forest realm of the Elves, protected by the power of Nenya
entities.culture: Ancient elven society focused on preservation and arts

entities.name: Nenya
entities.summary: The Ring of Water, one of the three Elven rings
entities.description: One of the Three Elven Rings, made of mithril with a white stone
entities.history: Crafted by Celebrimbor in the Second Age, given to Galadriel for safekeeping

entities.name: Gandalf
entities.summary: The Grey Wizard who later became Gandalf the White
entities.biography: One of the five Istari sent to Middle-earth to contest the power of Sauron

entities.name: Narya
entities.summary: The Ring of Fire, one of the three Elven rings
entities.description: One of the Three Elven Rings, set with a ruby
entities.history: Originally given to Círdan, who later passed it to Gandalf

entities.name: Isengard
entities.summary: The fortress of Saruman, containing the tower of Orthanc
entities.description: A great fortress at the southern end of the Misty Mountains, dominated by the tower of Orthanc
entities.culture: Originally Gondorian, later corrupted by Saruman

entities.name: Saruman
entities.summary: The chief of the Istari who fell to corruption
entities.biography: Originally the leader of the White Council, corrupted by his studies of Sauron's arts

entities.name: Battle of Helm's Deep
entities.summary: Major battle between the forces of Rohan and Saruman's army
entities.description: A decisive battle where the forces of Rohan defended the Hornburg against Saruman's army

entities.name: Frodo Baggins
entities.summary: The Ring-bearer who carried the One Ring to Mordor
entities.biography: A hobbit from the Shire who inherited the One Ring from his uncle Bilbo and undertook the quest to destroy it

entities.name: Minas Morgul
entities.summary: Former Gondorian city corrupted by the Nazgûl
entities.description: Originally Minas Ithil, captured by the forces of Sauron and transformed into a place of evil
entities.culture: Dominated by the Nazgûl and forces of Mordor

entities.name: Battle of the Pelennor Fields
entities.summary: The greatest battle of the War of the Ring
entities.description: The decisive battle before the gates of Minas Tirith between the forces of Gondor and Rohan against the armies of Mordor
consequences: Victory for the forces of the West

entities.name: Boromir
entities.summary: Captain of Gondor and member of the Fellowship of the Ring
entities.biography: Eldest son of Denethor II, Captain of the White Tower, and member of the Fellowship who fell defending Merry and Pippin

entities.name: Fangorn Forest
entities.summary: Ancient forest home to the Ents
entities.description: An ancient forest inhabited by Ents, located near Isengard
entities.culture: Domain of the Ents, ancient shepherds of trees

entities.name: Council of Elrond
entities.summary: Secret council where the fate of the One Ring was decided
entities.description: A secret council held in Rivendell to determine the fate of the One Ring
consequences: Formation of the Fellowship of the Ring
Decision to destroy the One Ring
Beginning of the Quest of the Ring

entities.name: Legolas
entities.summary: Elven prince of the Woodland Realm and member of the Fellowship
entities.biography: Son of King Thranduil, skilled archer and warrior who joined the Fellowship of the Ring

entities.name: Gimli
entities.summary: Dwarf warrior and member of the Fellowship of the Ring
entities.biography: Son of Glóin, representative of the dwarves in the Fellowship, who formed an unlikely friendship with Legolas

entities.name: Weathertop
entities.summary: Ancient watchtower where Frodo was wounded by the Witch-king
entities.description: Also known as Amon Sûl, an ancient watchtower of Arnor, site of a significant confrontation with the Nazgûl

entities.name: Battle of the Five Armies
entities.summary: The great battle for the capital of Gondor during the War of the Ring
entities.description: A major battle where the forces of Mordor besieged Minas Tirith, culminating in the arrival of the Rohirrim and Aragorn's forces

entities.name: Merry Brandybuck
entities.summary: A hobbit of the Shire who joined the Fellowship and became a knight of Rohan
entities.biography: Meriadoc Brandybuck, friend of Frodo who joined the Fellowship and later served under King Théoden of Rohan

entities.name: Peregrin Took
entities.summary: A hobbit of the Shire who became a Guard of the Citadel in Gondor
entities.biography: Youngest member of the Fellowship who later became a Guard of the Citadel and fought in the Battle of the Pelennor Fields

entities.name: Théoden
entities.summary: King of Rohan who led his people in the War of the Ring
entities.biography: King of Rohan who was freed from Saruman's influence and died heroically at the Battle of the Pelennor Fields

entities.name: Rohan
entities.summary: Kingdom of the Horse-lords, allies of Gondor
entities.description: A kingdom of skilled horsemen and warriors, known for its vast grasslands and cavalry
entities.culture: Horse-based society focused on martial prowess and honor

entities.name: Edoras
entities.summary: Capital city of Rohan, home to the Golden Hall of Meduseld
entities.description: The capital of Rohan, built upon a hill, dominated by the golden hall of Meduseld
entities.culture: Center of Rohirrim culture and governance

entities.name: Battle of Isengard
entities.summary: The Ents' assault on Isengard that ended Saruman's power
entities.description: The destruction of Isengard by the Ents, led by Treebeard, ending Saruman's industrial warfare
consequences: Flooding of the ring of Isengard

entities.name: Glamdring
entities.summary: The sword of Gandalf, an ancient Elvish blade
entities.description: An ancient Elvish sword, also known as Foe-hammer, wielded by Gandalf
entities.history: Originally forged for the Goblin-wars, found in a troll-hoard and claimed by Gandalf

entities.name: Éowyn
entities.summary: Shieldmaiden of Rohan who slew the Witch-king of Angmar
entities.biography: Niece of King Théoden, who disguised herself as a man to fight in the Battle of the Pelennor Fields

entities.name: Witch-king of Angmar
entities.summary: Leader of the Nazgûl and Sauron's most powerful servant
entities.biography: Once a great king of Men corrupted by one of the Nine Rings, became the Lord of the Nazgûl

entities.name: Barad-dûr
entities.summary: The Dark Tower, Sauron's greatest fortress in Mordor
entities.description: Massive fortress in Mordor, seat of Sauron's power and the location of the Eye
entities.culture: Center of Sauron's military and administrative power

entities.name: Sting
entities.summary: Bilbo's and later Frodo's elvish dagger that glows in the presence of orcs
entities.description: An ancient elvish dagger that glows blue when orcs are near
entities.history: Originally found in a troll-hoard, given to Bilbo by Gandalf, later passed to Frodo

entities.name: Battle of the Black Gate
entities.summary: The final major battle of the War of the Ring
entities.description: The last battle before the Black Gate of Mordor, serving as a diversion for Frodo's quest
consequences: Allowed time for the Ring's destruction

entities.name: Faramir
entities.summary: Captain of Gondor and younger son of Denethor
entities.biography: Younger brother of Boromir, Captain of the Rangers of Ithilien, later Prince of Ithilien and Steward of Gondor

entities.name: Palantír
entities.summary: Ancient seeing-stones used for communication and viewing distant lands
entities.description: Powerful spherical stones used to communicate across vast distances and see events in other places
entities.history: Created by the Noldor in Valinor, brought to Middle-earth by the Númenóreans

entities.name: Osgiliath
entities.summary: Ancient capital of Gondor, later reduced to ruins
entities.description: Former capital of Gondor spanning the river Anduin, largely in ruins by the time of the War of the Ring
entities.culture: Once the heart of Gondorian civilization, later a strategic military position

entities.name: Elrond
entities.summary: Lord of Rivendell and keeper of Vilya
entities.biography: Half-elven lord of Rivendell, keeper of the Ring of Air, and one of the wisest beings in Middle-earth

entities.name: Rivendell
entities.summary: The Last Homely House East of the Sea, realm of Elrond
entities.description: Hidden valley sanctuary of the elves, home to great lore and healing
entities.culture: Ancient elven society focused on knowledge, healing, and arts

entities.name: Vilya
entities.summary: The Ring of Air, mightiest of the Three Elven rings
entities.description: The most powerful of the Three Elven Rings, wielded by Elrond
entities.history: Crafted by Celebrimbor, given to Gil-galad who passed it to Elrond

entities.name: Denethor
entities.summary: Last Ruling Steward of Gondor
entities.biography: Last Ruling Steward of Gondor, father of Boromir and Faramir, driven to madness by use of the Palantír

entities.name: Fall of Gondolin
entities.summary: The destruction of the hidden elven city of Gondolin
entities.description: The siege and destruction of the hidden city of Gondolin by Morgoth's forces
consequences: Destruction of the greatest elven city

entities.name: Treebeard
entities.summary: Eldest of the Ents, shepherd of the forest
entities.biography: The oldest of the Ents, guardian of Fangorn Forest who led the attack on Isengard

entities.name: Narsil
entities.summary: The sword that was broken, later reforged as Andúril
entities.description: Ancient sword of Elendil that cut the One Ring from Sauron's hand
entities.history: Forged by Telchar of Nogrod, wielded by Elendil, broken in battle against Sauron

entities.name: Bilbo Baggins
entities.summary: The hobbit who found the One Ring and passed it to Frodo
entities.biography: A respectable hobbit who went on an unexpected journey and found the One Ring in Gollum's cave

entities.name: Bag End
entities.summary: The luxurious hobbit-hole home of Bilbo and later Frodo Baggins
entities.description: A comfortable and well-appointed hobbit-hole in Hobbiton, known for its green door and brass knob

entities.name: Finding of the Ring
entities.summary: Bilbo's discovery of the One Ring in Gollum's cave
entities.description: The moment when Bilbo Baggins found the One Ring in Gollum's cave beneath the Misty Mountains
consequences: Ring passed from Gollum to Bilbo
Beginning of the Ring's journey to destruction
Change in the fate of Middle-earth

entities.name: Mithril Coat
entities.summary: The precious mithril mail shirt given to Frodo by Bilbo
entities.description: A coat of mail made from mithril, light as a feather but stronger than dragon scales
entities.history: Made by the Dwarves of Moria, given to Bilbo by Thorin, later passed to Frodo

entities.name: Gollum
entities.summary: Former hobbit corrupted by the One Ring
entities.biography: Once a Stoor hobbit named Sméagol, corrupted by the One Ring which he possessed for centuries
